es & Sue Perrotto\n|WrittenBy       = Kaz, Kim Roberson, Aliki Theofilopoulos Grafft & John Mathot\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|4|15}}\n|ProdCode        = 406\n|Aux4            = 2.98<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/03/04/fridays-cable-ratings-nba-doubleheader-disney-originals-top-charts-176315/cable_20130301/|title=Friday's Cable Ratings: NBA Doubleheader, Disney Originals Top Charts|date=March 4, 2013|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=December 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|ShortSummary    = Agent P teams up with a former partner, a human agent named Lyla, to stop a hijacked train running along the U.S./Canada border. In a past mission, they had a falling out, so Agent P must decide whether or not he can trust Lyla and her unique sense of logic to get them through the mission, defeat Doofenshmirtz and save the train's passengers and Canada's national treasure \u2013 a moose named Albert.\n|LineColor       = 9600B8\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Phineas and Ferb (season 4)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 182\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n|Title           = Primal Perry\n|RTitle          = {{Refn|group=nb|name=\"Halfhour\"}}\n|DirectedBy      = Robert F. Hughes\n|WrittenBy       = Joshua Pruett & Kyle Menke \n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|5|6}}{{Refn|group=nb|name=\"XDBeforeChannel3\"|This episode premiered on Disney XD prior to Disney Channel. The episode premiered on Disney Channel on May 17, 2013.}}\n|ProdCode        = 408\n|Aux4            = <span style=\"color: grey;\"><small>N/A</small></span>\n|ShortSummary    = Perry must escape Liam, an Australian platypus hunter who is out to destroy him, rescue ongoing foe Dr. Doofenshmirtz from the error of his ways and maintain the sanctity of the Danville Botanical Gardens. Meanwhile, Phineas and Ferb create an \"infinite probability generator\" that allows Baljeet to make as many choices as he pleases without being affected by the consequences. This proves to be disastrous for Buford as the over 30 Baljeets